<br>
My opinion to fix warriors:  Give them full time defensive at 51+, and then increase the speed of the taunt (and maybe a boost to it)....  - thats for WARRIORs only (not Knights)<br>
<br>
If a warrior is taking less damage, even tho he can't taunt as well as Knights, people will want him simply becuase he is taking less damage and thus easier to heal (meaning the cleric can do something else - if there is no cleric, you could use a druid/shaman in place (since they won't need those bigger heals a cleric has...)) - By that alone, you've made shamans and druids a viable option again as main healers - Assuming they had a warrior as the main tank...<br>
<br>
As for monks, I would like to see a damage output increase ...  But a mitigation decrease (yes, another...) - OR - better yet, a mitigation decrease from the FRONT quarter only.  (ie. if they're pulling, they won't get hit as much...   But if they try and tank, they'll get creamed...)<br>
<br>
Not sure about Rogues - everyone complains they need more damage, but Non-AAXP Rogues are still outdamaging rangers with AM3 and EQ...  *shrug*<br>
<br>
