<br>
Next most broken class is warrior. Warrior taunt works fine with a decent warrior, but the best warrior cannot taunt as well as a knight. Knight = 100% effective and efficient taunting, something even the best equipped warrior can never match. As such, knights will get chosen over warriors.<br>
<br>
Least most broken of the pure melees is the rogues. We have some itemisation issues. We are really annoyed that sense and disarm trap skills are a) still pretty much useless and b) now shared with a whole bunch of other classes. Poisons are still a bit of a joke. Rogues are still the worst soloers in the game. The line between sustained damage and burst damage has been irretrievably blurred. Other classes do more or less equal damage as us AND have spells / utility. We still don't tank much better than a caster. All of this stuff is non critical, but it adds up. The problem with rogues is that they have been bleeding for a long time. SOE needs to get round to bandaging them. We can outdamage other classes in favourable situations, but not by enough to make up for the lack of utility. Rogues don't need a big fix, they just need some tweakage. If they don't get a fix, they will fall further and further behind and tweakage will no longer be enough to save them.<br>
<br>
Getting back to the topic, its funny but I don't see hardly any mages around these days either. Maybe they are all soloing??<br>
<br>
