<br>
<br>
Sure its nice to get some utility spells but many of those are available via items.  Rogues are not a broken class at all.  Then again being a bard I have all the utility stuff but will never hope to match the DPS of even the worst rogues.<br>
<br>
Class balance is something you are not going to see.  Certain classes like warriors fill a certain niche in the game.  They excel at one thing, tanking.  Making them better tanks would trivialize way too many encounters.  Then you will just have to deal with monsters that do even stupider things to counter the unbalanced tanks.  The warriors I am used to playing with almost never lose aggro.  So Sony puts in mobs that do things like randomly mem-wipe to make things interesting.<br>
<br>
I know its tough on younger seasoned warriors because they are so gear dependant.  But verant is making things easier with the expansions.  Now anyone can get SSRA or Vex Thal quality gear just from going thru some fairly easy adventures.  Aggro procs can be augmented to weapons and I even saw a plate breastplate that can be augmented with well over 200 hit points.  That puts even non-raiders on equal footing with any guild pre PoP.<br>
<br>
