<br>
&quot;I don't see a problem with rogues at all. A well equipped rogue will parse higher DPS than any other class in the game.&quot; - By and large true, provided the situations are favourable (i.e. we're fighting in LDoN and not Luclin) but would you rather have 10 extra dps or a whole bunch of spells? Rogues do better dps but not by a large margin. Add into that the fact that a rogue cannot really increase beyond a 16 dam piercer without entering the elementals. Which is sort of fine, except that a rogue relies so heavily on his or her damage. It's not like spells where you can hunt for runes in BoT and eventually get all your 65 spells, or even like FT where there are quite a lot of FT items floating about and you can save up for them... buying a 17 or higher damage piercer just isn't realistic. If you want a 17 damage piercer you have to be in the elemental planes. So there's a sort of inherent cap on rogue power, a cap that most other classes do not feel to the same degree, especially now that LDoN came out allowing a lot of classes alternative upgrade routes. (To my knowledge, highest damage piercer in LDoN is 16).<br>
<br>
&quot;SoS is one of the most powerful AA in the game.&quot; - And yet is almost entirely useless. I can drag a corpse. I can go places that no other classes can go and when I get there I can turn around and come back because there is NOTHING that I can do there on my own =) I might be good for scouting in LDoN, but actually any wizard eye is better.<br>
<br>
&quot;Sure its nice to get some utility spells but many of those are available via items.&quot; - Don't make me laugh. Next you're going to say that I get utility via poisons.<br>
<br>
&quot;Rogues are not a broken class at all.&quot; - They need tweaking. They aren't broken as such, but they do need some improvements.<br>
<br>
&quot;Then again being a bard I have all the utility stuff but will never hope to match the DPS of even the worst rogues.&quot; - But I bet you can get a group much easier than even the best rogues =)<br>
<br>
Sorry to sound haughty and patronising, but there's a lot of myths about rogues (as I'm sure there are about most classes). Don't mean anything by it, just clearing up a few points =)<br>
